# Backend API Client Module

## PURPOSE
Client-side API layer for communicating with backend server.
Handles all HTTP requests for user management, payments, and data sync.

## CONTAINS
- client.js: Base API client with auth headers
- user.js: User account operations (register, login, profile)
- payment.js: Payment processing (Stripe integration)
- subscription.js: Sync subscription data with backend

## RESPONSIBILITIES
- Authenticate API requests with JWT tokens
- Handle user registration and login
- Process payment transactions
- Track user's run count and payment status
- Sync subscription data to backend
- Handle API errors and retries

## REFERENCES
- Parent: /src/.windsurf
- Root: /.windsurf
- Connects to: /backend/* (server-side API)

## RULES
- Always include auth tokens in requests
- Handle 401 (unauthorized) by refreshing token
- Retry failed requests with exponential backoff
- Never store sensitive data in localStorage
- Use HTTPS only for API calls
- Validate responses before using data
